- Develop a tool that offers readers interesting questions about the content and learns iteratively what users are interested in.
- Consider generating Q&A questions at the end of an article to prompt further exploration.
- Create an outline feature for blogs, similar to Wikipedia's table of contents.
- Live in the future and build things that are interesting to bridge gaps between the future and present.
- Notice what's missing or could be done better in everyday life to develop solutions.
- Don't underestimate competition, as it can be a sign of market demand.
- Embrace doing hard and unappealing work because it could be valued and clear roadblocks.
- Avoid using recipes for ideas, and instead look for demand and explore why certain things aren't there.